                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-355-off1828 t18300916-355-crimeloc1831"></join>. On the 6th of August I was returning to my shop, about twelve o'clock - I saw a man standing one door from my shop, and as I got to my door I met the prisoner coming out with this glass; I went and asked my wife if she had sold it - she said No; I followed the prisoner and the other man - he threw the glass against a fence; I pursued, and took him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The looking-glass was standing at the door. Witness. No, it was inside, on a wash-hand stand.</p>
               <p>
            
